

# Conventional Commit Guide
#   https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/#summary
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# STRUCTURE:
# <type>[!]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# TYPES:
#    feat:     New feature
#    fix:      Bugfix
#    perf:     Efficiency and latency tuning
#    chore:    Maintenance, tooling, and deps
#    refactor: Cleanup (no behavior change)
#    docs:     Documentation only
#
#    Append ! for breaking changes
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# SIMPLE EXAMPLE:
#    chore: tighten eslint rules
#
# COMPLEX EXAMPLE (breaking change + body):
#    chore!: upgrade TypeScript to v6
#
#    v6 enables stricter null checks by default. Several utility
#    functions required explicit return type annotations that were
#    previously inferred. Consumers of this shell will need to
#    audit their own code after upgrading.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
